                <h1>What’s in a Name: The Origins of Pickleball</h1>
                <p>The term "pickleball" is believed to come from the name of a dog belonging to one of the sport's co-founders, Joel Pritchard. "Pickles" would chase after the balls during gameplay. Other theories suggest it derives from "pickle boat," a crew term for a mixed team. Regardless, the quirky name adds to the charm of this fun sport!</p>
